<subSubSection id="073B82ED6BB2C51B20B6F86F75E6CCD9" pageId="7" pageNumber="86" type="derivation of specific epithet">
<paragraph id="931DDA1B9ABAFA223ADF58C412A7A145" pageId="7" pageNumber="86">Derivation of specific epithet.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="19F585DC7D713E03490DC37C682A5C98" pageId="7" pageNumber="86">
The epithet 
<normalizedToken id="97B612CC41FFB7AAC4FFF612EEE1494B" originalValue="“bellorum”">
&quot; 
<emphasis id="0541B3FE9E4E343738BA9D8CEB1015A0" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="86">bellorum</emphasis>
&quot;
</normalizedToken>
is an eponym, based on the family name of Ross and Joyce Bell, with a special thanks for a career that brought light to the rhysodine clade of very interesting beetles with colors and tough cuticle also found in adults of 
<taxonomicName id="473009BF05FD6DB4285AD105F8DE9281" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1872" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Mizotrechus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C2931EECA33C65FE480FD6C1998CFFDD" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="86">Mizotrechus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
